Field Marshal Erwin Rommel gained respect from his foes for his tactical acumen and sense of fairness during the battle for North Africa .
The German field marshal was captured with 2,000 of his men by Rommel in Mechili, Libya, in 1941 .
They were given to him by a British prisoner as a gift to thank him for retrieving a stolen hat .
Now the story of how the German came to be in possession of the goggles can be told for the first time .